w problem.","e":"aware","pos":3,"m":"biết, nhận thức, nhận thức thấy"},{"om":"to or at a distance from somebody/something in space or time","p":"əˈweɪ","ex":"The beach is a mile away.","e":"away","pos":4,"m":"xa, xa cách, rời xa, đi xa"},{"om":"very bad or unpleasant","p":"ˈɔːfl","ex":"That's an awful colour.","e":"awful","pos":3,"m":"oai nghiêm, dễ sợ"},{"om":"making you feel embarrassed","p":"ˈɔːkwərd","ex":"There was an awkward silence.","e":"awkward","pos":3,"m":"vụng về, lung túng"},{"om":"to move or make something move backwards","p":"bæk","ex":"He backed against the wall, terrified.","e":"back","m":"lưng, về phía sau, trở lại"},{"om":"the details of a person's family, education, experience, etc","p":"ˈbækɡraʊnd","ex":"a person's family/social/cultural/educational/class background","e":"background","pos":1,"m":"phía sau; nền"},{"om":"towards a place or position that is behind","p":"ˈbækwərdz","ex":"I lost my balance and fell backwards.","e":"backwards","m":"Về phía sau, giật lùi\nChậm tiến, lạc hậu","pos":4,"syn":["around","back","rearward","backward","round"]},{"om":"directed or moving towards the back","p":"ˈbækwərd","ex":"She strode past him without a backward glance.","e":"backward","pos":3,"m":"về phía sau, lùi lại"},{"om":"the simplest and smallest forms of life.Bacteria exist in large numbers in air, water and soil, and also in living and dead creatures and plants, and are often a cause of disease","p":"bækˈtɪriə","ex":"bacterial infections/growth","e":"bacteria","pos":1,"m":"vi khuẩn"},{"om":"unpleasant; full of problems","p":"bæd","ex":"bad news/weather/dreams/habits","e":"bad","pos":3,"m":"xấu, tồi"},{"om":"not skilfully or not carefully","p":"ˈbædli","ex":"to play/sing badly","e":"badly","pos":4,"m":"xấu, tồi"},{"om":"often angry; in an angry mood","ex":"She gets very bad-tempered when she's tired.","e":"bad-tempered","pos":3,"m":"xấu tính, dễ nổi cáu"},{"om":"a container made of paper or plastic, that opens at the top, used especially in shops/stores","p":"bæɡ","ex":"a plastic/polythene/paper bag","e":"bag","pos":1,"m":"bao, túi, cặp xách"},{"om":"the beliefs and attitudes that somebody has as a result of their past experiences","p":"ˈbæɡɪdʒ","ex":"excess baggage (= weighing more than the limit allowed on a plane)","e":"baggage","pos":1,"m":"hành lý"},{"om":"to cook food in an oven without extra fat or liquid; to be cooked in this way","p":"beɪk","ex":"baked apples","e":"bake","pos":2,"m":"nung, nướng bằng lò"},{"om":"to put your body or something else into a position where it is steady and does not fall","p":"ˈbæləns","ex":"How long can you balance on one leg?","e":"balance","m":"cái cân; làm cho cân bằng, tương xứng"},{"om":"a round object used for throwing, hitting or kicking in games and sports","p":"bɔːl","ex":"a golf/tennis/cricket ball","e":"ball","pos":1,"m":"quả bóng"},{"om":"an official rule that says that something is not allowed","p":"bæn","ex":"There is to be a total ban on smoking in the office.","e":"ban","m":"cấm, cấm chỉ; sự cấm"},{"om":"a small group of musicians who play popular music together, often with a singer or singers","p":"bænd","ex":"a rock/jazz band","e":"band","pos":1,"m":"băng, đai, nẹp"}]